{"chapters":{"1":{"heading":"10 questions for Maine","content":[{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"From our parks, real and proposed, to our policies, politics and prominent people, Maine faces some serious \u2014 and whimsical \u2014 questions in 2016. Will divisive issues be decided? In a fight between city hall and a casino, who wins? How will decisions from last year, about tests, wages and mayors, echo into the new? There\u2019s much to consider over the coming months, and more will emerge. For now, these 10 questions should start the conversation."}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"2":{"heading":"Could a national park be declared?","content":[{"filename":"16348079.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Gabor Degre | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"Plans for a Katahdin-region national park may have been stymied, but are not defeated. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/11\/16\/news\/penobscot\/st-clair-national-monument-could-be-step-toward-park\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEbBxUrdbrn6kWbDRxKF4rqXFBrxQ\">There\u2019s now organized lobbying in Washington, D.C<\/a>., and <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/11\/10\/news\/penobscot\/national-park-advocates-unveil-petition-to-maine-delegation\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG4tFfoGWl15LAKIFRFY9h5IPFnqg\">a public campaign in Maine<\/a>. And with the 100th anniversary of the National Park Service, and President Barack Obama\u2019s last year in office, there\u2019s talk of an executive order creating a \u201cnational monument\u201d \u2014 a park precursor \u2014 in Maine. The prospect is real enough to have <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/08\/31\/politics\/lepage-tells-obama-to-steer-clear-of-national-park-debate\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFpxfFkcoYM7eb0NJ7AYyfhdYriXA\">Gov. Paul LePage<\/a>, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/11\/23\/politics\/collins-king-poliquin-express-serious-reservations-about-north-woods-national-monument\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFGSUvVyheKftG2-fFbRpQxyBzV_w\">Sens. Susan Collins and Angus King, and U.S. Rep. Bruce Poliquin<\/a>\u00a0come out early against any plan. The national park is a dividing issue. Who should decide whether it exists? An answer may come in 2016."}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"3":{"heading":"What if Caribou splits?","content":[{"filename":"15311347.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Julia Bayly | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"One of the most overlooked but important stories in Maine is playing out in Caribou, where a <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2014\/07\/16\/news\/aroostook\/group-of-rural-taxpayers-unveils-plan-to-secede-from-caribou\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHtVG1-XWzA2jBF0Jrc1H_hKU-_Og\">group of citizens is petitioning to split the city\u2019s rural outskirts into a new town: Lyndon<\/a>. Why does this matter? While the cleaving of any community is serious, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/03\/20\/the-point\/crying-secession-in-maine-how-state-policies-fuel-municipal-division\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHuljeU9EMt-t92cK40F--L4rhc_w\">a divorce of urban and rural exemplifies growing tensions in Maine<\/a>. More so than ever, our state is divided between north and south, east and west, prosperous and struggling, growing and graying. It\u2019s reflected in our political speech and preferences, our economic data and census figures. Yet Maine is strongest together, as a state and people, united for the improvement of our standing. If a rock-ribbed community like Caribou can split along these lines, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/07\/03\/the-point\/if-a-town-cant-afford-to-be-a-town-it-may-make-sense-to-disband\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEc5CruwV2fqvnO9wswGEWWx7VYgQ\">what does it say for the rest of Maine<\/a>?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"4":{"heading":"What\u2019s next for the mayors? ","content":[{"filename":"16302101.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Troy R. Bennett | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"One is a polished politico, the other anything but. One is left, the other right. Yet <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/11\/03\/politics\/elections\/strimling-vaults-into-early-lead-in-portland\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFdENmfzcQBWAoE4d15kz57hjGYqg\">Ethan Strimling <\/a>and <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/video\/robert-macdonald-bests-ben-chin-in-race-for-lewiston-mayor\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGz5tPA-CsXQplhsV3UgbEn9BjvgQ\">Robert Macdonald<\/a>\u00a0have much in common: They are mayors of Maine\u2019s largest cities \u2014 Portland and Lewiston \u2014 who triumphed in high-profile races against powerful opponents. Strimling toppled incumbent Mike Brennan, while Macdonald defeated a hard-charging young progressive. Both are now under scrutiny after the attention heaped on their campaigns. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/09\/04\/opinion\/editorials\/cities-are-the-way-of-maines-future-maine-must-embrace-that-reality\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNF8ugX_3Fl23QKtYdXs8v6yk7lS2Q\">Maine needs strong cities to thrive<\/a>\u00a0and their mayors to work together. (<a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.sunjournal.com\/news\/lewiston-auburn\/0001\/11\/30\/robert-macdonald-wins-third-term-lewiston-mayor\/1832411&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEjiWc1Igf87kWht5SnD15RHBew_w\">Macdonald, for his part, said he\u2019s looking forward to working with Strimling<\/a>.) Will it\u00a0happen?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"5":{"heading":"Will Acadia have a happy 100th? ","content":[{"filename":"16138613.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Aislinn Sarnacki | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"When it was 99, Acadia National Park had a very good year. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/10\/02\/news\/hancock\/park-pressure-acadia-considers-new-controls-as-visits-unique-uses-rise\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGV0jOFQH1Fskwv_dPR0HnDXdt-6A\">Visits were expected to crest 2.5 million<\/a>, the most since 1999. Plus, some 1,400 acres and a new oceanfront campground on the <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/11\/18\/news\/hancock\/acadia-to-take-ownership-of-1400-acres-on-schoodic-peninsula\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEWFJJbD61ib5Ncv3D-Eisbg0sSEQ\">Schoodic peninsula were added<\/a>. Not everything was rosy, though. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/09\/16\/news\/hancock\/acadia-national-park-grapples-with-traffic-congestion\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE7GTePuBttKM6tmAAufxQW1HRVZw\">Congestion on Cadillac Mountain closed its summit to vehicle traffic six times<\/a>. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/afterthecouch.bangordailynews.com\/2015\/08\/17\/ranger-says-group-of-7-runners-heading-up-cadillac-needed-permit\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG8DiOALi1RvoLwiXQQRlLTQ5-mxQ\">An innocuous group run<\/a>\u00a0sparked <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/10\/20\/news\/hancock\/acadia-amends-rules-for-group-activities\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG1h9SWmM3lnayMR-JlL2c6YvSyYQ\">unprecedented regulations<\/a>\u00a0and debate about new pressures on Maine\u2019s national park. When Acadia turns 100 in July later this year, could these trends mean a big party, and big problems, on Mount Desert Island?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"6":{"heading":"What are Bangor\u2019s odds? ","content":[{"filename":"14992805.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Ashley L. Conti | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"Beating the house is every gambler\u2019s dream, and what Bangor aims to do. This year, whether <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/04\/23\/news\/bangor\/hollywood-casino-asks-bangor-to-cut-property-value-36-8-million\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGvZTeX6uMVW-IrpJkubVQv-FwVvA\">Hollywood Casino receives a staggering tax abatement<\/a>\u00a0\u2014 <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/05\/22\/business\/bangor-says-casinos-valuation-when-changing-hands-doesnt-justify-abatement-request\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFF8ReUk7nnnq2t78Y73-oYRVgmJw\">based on its own calculation of the value of its hotel and casino<\/a>\u00a0\u2014 <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/10\/29\/business\/bangor-casino-raises-stakes-in-tax-dispute-with-city\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGFd3oc6dxDd0_zIMLmfp51DliD2A\">will be be decided<\/a>. This process is <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.bostonglobe.com\/metro\/2015\/10\/31\/maine-casino-operator-tax-break-plea-could-omen-for-massachusetts\/IFQk8ALsOnJDlMINW5DfbK\/story.html&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEY7UN3egYTpXiEvS0gnFC1LKDO8g\">being watched around New England<\/a>, where a spate of new casinos has saturated the market and tightened revenues. If Bangor\u2019s gambit fails, other casinos try to cut their tax payments. If the city wins, casinos may lose the chance to outline the art of the deal. Who do the oddsmakers favor?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"7":{"heading":"Does \u201cas Maine goes\u201d still matter? ","content":[{"filename":"15390813.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Ashley L. Conti | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"Is the old chestnut, \u201cAs Maine goes, so goes the nation,\u201d fading into anachronism? The Pine Tree State\u2019s influence in national elections has stemmed from <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2008\/10\/26\/politics\/why-maine-splits-its-electoral-votes\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEeoW1kGdovLQYpxw068ODd2kqO7g\">a quirk of the Electoral College, as Maine is one of two states to award its delegates by congressional district, not as a unit<\/a>. So in a close election, where one or two Electoral College votes could make the difference, maybe Maine could have an outsized effect if, for the first time, its votes split. Or will the presidential election be final evidence that as Maine goes, the nation goes its own way?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"8":{"heading":"How much can one ballot fit? ","content":[{"filename":"6136690.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Kate Collins | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"Welcome to the year of<a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/12\/03\/the-point\/maine-signature-gatherers-race-to-beat-winter-filing-deadline\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG5nh8Ek5IUqJOCrgk9RCl2U3GL4w\">\u00a0citizen-initiated referendums<\/a>.\u00a0In 2016, Mainers could decide <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D5%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjB0NC4poTKAhUGLSYKHVSNAD8QFgg1MAQ%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F10%252F26%252Fpolitics%252Fmaine-marijuana-legalization-groups-agree-to-work-together%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGPN0nQUMSocF2je0Z0vy_0dYQlRA%26sig2%3DGvju6iUmC1OAQSONiWl2wQ%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEcgGmkZfkZMmsRYFPRKI5Tvq6Geg\">marijuana legalization<\/a>, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D1%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjXva3EpoTKAhUKLSYKHSJUAfEQFggdMAA%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fstateandcapitol.bangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F10%252F21%252Fwill-mainers-vote-to-increase-school-funding-by-157-million-in-2016%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNEff7h2nL_FGb1H7iU0kLlgsOSllw%26sig2%3DBI-3q2CHYrYfisY1QMTVEQ&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFdG8qsZaPlfRWEsScLAPrzpmvPdA\">education funding<\/a>, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D1%26ved%3D0ahUKEwj94aHSpoTKAhWJ0iYKHQ34BUsQFggcMAA%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F08%252F24%252Fpolitics%252Fgroup-aims-for-2016-maine-vote-on-gun-sales-background-checks%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGZI00m2kyOnhM0KAtI7X3Rw8sstg%26sig2%3DpAIV0iA5PbObq4MKQ4WnYw%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEZzRXf6aD-RveQ_MHcBaSBZI8VpA\">gun control<\/a>, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D2%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjM6IjcpoTKAhVM4CYKHbQ1A_0QFggjMAE%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F11%252F27%252Fpolitics%252Fmaine-gop-scrambles-to-meet-petition-deadline-for-tax-welfare-ballot-question%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGQIeypLdXvW7Ud_LKxYJV3YfC45A%26sig2%3DwJelbPX40v-156huYHcHmA%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHDBbxV2TSvNJc0EXbn84o2IJhejA\">welfare reform, income tax rates<\/a>, <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D8%26ved%3D0ahUKEwi7sfrypoTKAhVH4SYKHWxeCeUQFghPMAc%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F04%252F16%252Fpolitics%252Freferendum-launched-for-12-maine-minimum-wage-by-2020%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNFONvWJeh3Sn9y3ZZdg7_AzYRpqPQ%26sig2%3DAF4pCVEwUL0vzt4UcxvPJg%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEVuvDFOlwBT_cbSVwba6Us0cJ9mA\">minimum wage<\/a>\u00a0and <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D1%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjp7-uAp4TKAhWIwiYKHUlUCEIQFggcMAA%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F11%252F18%252Fpolitics%252Franked-choice-voting-question-certified-for-maines-november-2016-ballot%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNEOMVIDTa8b7K95pTDt5D06HV9vsw%26sig2%3DtwraaFTId-e-lE_SDmDpzA%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNECBg0WuqNGAogCP5OYh8oX17luYA\">ranked-choice voting<\/a>\u00a0on one ballot. It is too much? If so, here\u2019s an alternative: A Maine Town Meeting. We all gather one Saturday in our schools, grange halls, town offices and community centers to decide these questions like articles on a warrant. After all, if the people are going to decide these anyway, because our elected representatives can\u2019t agree, doesn\u2019t this make sense? It\u2019s a perfect blend of two Maine traditions: Participatory democracy and potluck cuisine. Pass the voter cards and baked beans, please."}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"9":{"heading":"Will this sequel end differently?","content":[{"filename":"13797687.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Troy R. Bennett | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"\u00a0"},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"It seems as if U.S. Rep. Bruce Poliquin had barely arrived in Congress when rumors flew that his 2014 challenger, former state Sen. Emily Cain, wanted a rematch. The rumors were prescient, a<a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D3%26ved%3D0ahUKEwic24Cqp4TKAhWDRSYKHVE-DowQFggrMAI%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F03%252F04%252Fthe-point%252Fwhy-emily-cain-announced-another-congressional-bid-so-early%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNFHPxoBnOS0g2MIW6pn-0kkhBAjfg%26sig2%3D-gzTjYZ0M0GyYy35rQrJOQ%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHzJ0v3V4HYf9onQRP29EUKCaalaw\">s Cain has pursued Poliquin with vigor throughout the latter\u2019s inaugural term<\/a>. Yet a question remains: What\u2019s different this time? Cain is\u00a0an experienced legislator, liked and respected by a core constituency. But Poliquin <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D8%26ved%3D0ahUKEwiZr5qNp4TKAhUCKCYKHdusDQkQFghOMAc%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F10%252F12%252Fnews%252Fstate%252Fpoliquins-re-election-war-chest-nears-total-for-2014-campaign%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNHy2WtaUthNoe_eF7-1qp9R85heyA%26sig2%3DuXP3_-Q2A_04rEXDn7_YIg%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNH7aIyhIM9xBuj0jMYirj1pWc_r3Q\">has proved a skillful retail politician and connected with voters across the vast 2nd District, especially on economic issues<\/a>. If she fends off a <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D1%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjDs5HFp4TKAhXCSiYKHaCFA8MQFggcMAA%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F07%252F29%252Fpolitics%252Fbangor-city-councilor-joe-baldacci-to-run-for-us-house-seat%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGJS29tUtwyNewu6MOr6JKDZt6iOQ%26sig2%3DTLZyh3-iieDvNdHSkm02jw%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG8OwjdRnphp672JToq2IdTjC1FoA\">primary challenger, Bangor City Councilor Joe Baldacci<\/a>, she will then have the tough task of unseating a well-financed incumbent. Is her road to Washington any easier? It appears not."}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"10":{"heading":"Can Maine stick to a test?","content":[{"filename":"12825387.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Nell Gluckman | BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"It\u2019s the $4 million question. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D2%26ved%3D0ahUKEwj89tjVp4TKAhWCQiYKHc6ODDoQFggjMAE%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F12%252F03%252Fnews%252Fstate%252Fmaine-signs-4-million-contract-for-standardized-tests%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGudz5CEsyzOgD-TkeJcNg2a30Myw%26sig2%3DLmMYVNhayx89ohHpw3c6XQ%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGbz4klL14Y1GUe198bEQmJX5Cspg\">The state has a new contract with a New Hampshire company, Measured Progress, to replace the controversial Smarter Balanced standardized tests used for a single year<\/a>. While there\u2019s little question the <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D4%26ved%3D0ahUKEwj89tjVp4TKAhWCQiYKHc6ODDoQFggxMAM%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F10%252F17%252Fthe-point%252Fmaine-didnt-do-so-well-on-the-smarter-balanced-test-the-hard-part-is-figuring-out-why%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNFAAHiWxiL2jV7kfcEokzOgvV6H-g%26sig2%3Dat2EmGDkE1A0x6XB-Ldeqg%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHIRGAhKV3ToJaBNJoGA5UeQXQQ-Q\">Smarter Balanced tests were a problem, it\u2019s just as problematic to skip from test to test and create voids and variables about Maine student performance<\/a>. Experts agree: <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D2%26ved%3D0ahUKEwiduf_sp4TKAhVI5iYKHTRQBLIQFggvMAE%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2013%252F11%252F10%252Fopinion%252Fcontributors%252Fwhy-three-businessmen-want-maine-to-invest-in-early-childhood-education%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNFfD4CPGyeZPilnNEjEESI2L7svoQ%26sig2%3DWzWk9cdv6bMb6TzNT_KhDw%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNH5H-1LUZCmF1TkHTobg5NjZX7JVg\">A key to Maine\u2019s future prosperity is early childhood education<\/a>. <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D10%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjz0aGBqITKAhXBNSYKHcjWCcwQFghbMAk%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F05%252F20%252Fopinion%252Fwhy-maine-shouldnt-give-up-on-smarter-balanced-testing%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNGaMaw77orDvei_513c4KcGeFS0aA%26sig2%3Ds36pbotNQC2IXvXa-VbaVw%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGkDYP91uyAGaN8t9wVOLJXd76NAw\">Ensuring this works means depending on data, testing, benchmarks and rigorous standards.<\/a>\u00a0Entering 2016, the resolution to stand behind a particular test seems critical. Will one stick?"}],"preview image":"","short title":""},"11":{"heading":"What happens after raising the minimum wage?","content":[{"filename":"16091161.jpg","filetype":"photo","size":"big","orientation":"full","caption":"","credit":"Darren Fishell| BDN","poster":""},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"Local minimum wage increases in Portland and Bangor made our top stories of 2015 because of their symbolic nature \u2014 <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D7%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjZu_-hqITKAhWKSCYKHSADAkkQFghGMAY%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F09%252F10%252Fbusiness%252Fportland-council-sets-minimum-wage-to-10-10-adjusts-tipped-wage%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNEjBLE89NMn3qAKXs-ppk1irotmDw%26sig2%3DHg-3Aushcg9Kjduhcsbs_w&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGe1GWkhP3ZIz0T05t-ewcmNBY4rw\">Portland\u2019s starts on Jan. 1<\/a>,<a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q%3Dhttp:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/12\/14\/news\/bangor\/city-council-votes-to-raise-bangors-minimum-wage\/%26sa%3DD%26ust%3D1451533870277000%26usg%3DAFQjCNFqCK6lFXOIzBPg4bbQsZarDStDiQ&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE7L4tcYtGW4mSCC6so1ywVOTGDtA\">\u00a0and Bangor\u2019s <\/a><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q%3Dhttp:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/12\/14\/news\/bangor\/city-council-votes-to-raise-bangors-minimum-wage\/%26sa%3DD%26ust%3D1451533870277000%26usg%3DAFQjCNFqCK6lFXOIzBPg4bbQsZarDStDiQ&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE7L4tcYtGW4mSCC6so1ywVOTGDtA\">not<\/a><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q%3Dhttp:\/\/bangordailynews.com\/2015\/12\/14\/news\/bangor\/city-council-votes-to-raise-bangors-minimum-wage\/%26sa%3DD%26ust%3D1451533870277000%26usg%3DAFQjCNFqCK6lFXOIzBPg4bbQsZarDStDiQ&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE7L4tcYtGW4mSCC6so1ywVOTGDtA\">\u00a0until 2017<\/a>. This year, the symbolism fades and the reality grows: <a class=\"c0\" href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D5%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjZu_-hqITKAhWKSCYKHSADAkkQFgg4MAQ%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fbangordailynews.com%252F2015%252F08%252F21%252Fthe-point%252Fquestion-for-portland-voters-whats-the-right-minimum-wage%252F%26usg%3DAFQjCNE9oZ_NzBcyFrOHHJj8NusuMD5jxg%26sig2%3DBITuTGd_33hmD-K9JrMheg%26bvm%3Dbv.110151844,d.eWE&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGXJaKfHgsXNtwOp3WfXZmJBh0rOg\">Portland\u2019s experience with a higher minimum wage will influence how the policy is adopted elsewhere<\/a>. Will certain businesses suffer or leave? Will new businesses be dissuaded from investing? Will this increase have a meaningful effect on those earning the minimum wage? How will the gap between state and local wage laws be policed? By this time next year, answers to all should emerge."},{"filename":null,"filetype":"text","size":null,"orientation":null,"caption":"\u00a0"}],"preview image":"","short title":""}}}